FBIS3-20408 "drweu062aa_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-062 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS French Troops Leave for Zagreb To Relieve Unit AU3103111894 Paris AFP in English 1104 GMT 31 Mar 94 AU3103111894 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Lille, France, March 31 (AFP) -- A contingent of 200 French troops left the northern French city of Lille for Zagreb Thursday [31 March] to relieve the 403d Logistical Support Detachment whose term of service in the former Yugoslavia is due to expire. The contingent, the first of three totalling 600 troops to leave for Zagreb over a three-day period, is headed by Lieutenant-Colonel Patrick Rose. France has a total of more than 6,000 men in the former Yugoslavia.
